HEADWORD: Abba
<hw>Ab"ba</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧b"b⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Syriac
<ets>abb⟦amac⟧</ets> father. See <er>Abbot</er>.]</ety> <def>Father;
religious superior; -- in the Syriac, Coptic, and Ethiopic churches, a
title given to the bishops, and by the bishops to the
patriarch.</def>⟦br⟧
